Easy Trader Joe’s meals apart 12: feta pasta. Save this post for later! 
So technically you can get these ingredients anywhere but I got them all at TJs! This recipe went viral on TikTok a while ago but I still make it all the time - it’s so good and so easy. 

Here’s what you’ll need:
• pasta of choice (I like rigatoni or cavatappi)
• block of feta (make sure you use a block and not the crumbles) 
• 2 containers of Roma tomatoes 
• 5 cloves of garlic 
• additional veggies if you want - I like to add red pepper 
and red onion 
• salt, pepper, garlic powder and Italian seasoning 
• olive oil 
• 1 cup of reserved pasta water 

Here’s what I did:
• place the block of feta in the middle of a baking dish. Add tomatoes, garlic, and extra veggies all around it 
• pour olive oil generously over the veggies and feta
• season with salt, pepper, garlic powder and Italian seasoning 
• stir the vegetables 
• bake at 350° for 45 minutes (the tomatoes should be soft and easily squish when done)
• cook your pasta while the feta + veggies cook. Make sure you reserve a cup of pasta water 
• once the feta + veggies are done, stir it all together until creamy. Add your pasta and stir. Add in the reserved pasta water. Start with a 1/4 of a cup and add more as needed to make the sauce creamier 
That’s it!

The easiest shredded chicken in the crockpot. Save this post for later!
We make this on a regular basis to use for meals throughout the week - it’s great for chicken salad, tacos, to add to a salad or wrap, and much more!

Here’s what you’ll need:
• 3 chicken breasts (frozen or thawed)
• chicken broth
• salt, pepper, garlic powder

Here’s what I did:
• place the 3 chicken breasts in the crockpot
• pour chicken broth over the chicken until it’s about halfway up the chicken
• season generously with salt, pepper, and garlic powder
• cook for 4 hours on high (if the chicken breasts are frozen) or 3 hours on low (if they’re thawed) 
• shred when done - I like to put the chicken breasts in the mixer and turn it on low for a couple of minutes. Shreds the chicken perfectly!

Easy Trader Joe’s appetizer - save this post for later! 
Looking for an easy and delicious app for Super Bowl Sunday?? I got you! This corn dip is so tasty and only takes a few minutes to prepare. It’s a little spicy, but I’m a baby when it comes to spice and I can handle it. 

Here’s what you’ll need:
• one block of cream cheese (I used reduced fat, but you can use regular or reduced fat)
• 1 jar of cowboy caviar 
• pepper jack cheese
• Mexican blend cheese 
• fire roasted corn (in the frozen aisle) 

Here’s what I did:
• melt the cream cheese in the microwave until soft and spreadable
• mix in an entire jar of cowboy caviar 
• mix in 3/4 cup of pepper jack cheese and 3/4 cup of Mexican blend cheese 
• pour into a 2 quart greased baking dish
• top with 1/4 cup of fire roasted corn and 1/4 cup of Mexican blend cheese 
• bake at 375° for 20-30 minutes 
• serve with your favorite tortilla chips (we love the elote chip, but it makes it even spicier)

Winter meal idea - homemade chicken pot pie. Save this post for later!
We made this recipe last year (a few times) and it was so good that we decided to make it a yearly tradition in the winter. 

Here’s what you need:
• 4 tablespoons unsalted butter
• 4 cups of shredded chicken (see my reel about how to make the best shredded chicken in the crockpot)
• 1 cup sliced carrots
• 1/2 cup sliced celery
• 1/2 cup chopped yellow onion
• 1 1/4 teaspoons salt
• 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder
• 1/2 teaspoon dried thyme leaves
• 1/4 teaspoon ground black pepper
• 1/4 cup all-purpose flour
• 1/2 cup heavy cream
• 1 cup chicken broth
• 1/2 cup frozen peas
• 2 (1 top and 1 bottom) unbaked pie crusts

Here’s what I did:
• preheat oven to 425°
• melt the butter in a pan. Add the carrots, celery, onion, salt, garlic powder, thyme leaves, and pepper. Cook for 8-10 minutes, stirring frequently 
• add the flour and stir well. Slowly stir in the cream, then add the chicken broth. Cook about 3-4 minutes until it thickens. Stir often
• remove from the heat and add the frozen peas. Let the filling cool for 30 minutes (or longer if you have the time)
• place one pie crust in the bottom of a pie dish and shape to the dish. Fill with cooled pot pie filling. 
• top with second pie crust and press the edges together. Cut a few slits in the top pie crust 
• bake for 30 minutes on the bottom rack of the oven 
• once done, let it cool for 20-30 minutes before digging in!

Easy brown butter Rice Krispies treats recipe - save this post for later! I’ve made these twice now this pregnancy because they’re so dang good. Seriously the best Rice Krispies treats I’ve ever had. 

Recipe credit: @saltandbaker 

Here’s what you need:
• 7 tablespoons of butter (I prefer salted butter)
• 10 cups mini marshmallows
• 1/4 teaspoon kosher salt
• 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract
• 6 cups Rice Krispies cereal

Here’s what I did:
• melt the butter in a large pot. Once melted, brown the butter for about 8 minutes on low. Stir frequently so that it doesn’t burn 
• once the butter bubbles and turns to a brownish color, stir in 8 cups of mini marshmallows 
• once the marshmallows have melted, add the salt and vanilla extra 
• remove from heat and stir in the Rice Krispies cereal. Add the additional 2 cups of mini marshmallows and mix together 
• line a 9x12 baking dish with parchment paper and spray with cooking spray to prevent sticking 
• pour the mixture into the dish and gently press it into the pan
• let the Rice Krispies cool for an hour or so. Cut and serve. Store in sealed Tupperware at room temperature.

Easy Trader Joe’s meals part 33: cheesesteak sandwiches. Save this post for later!

These were a big hit!! So easy and the meat only takes a few minutes to cook.

Here’s what you need:

• ciabatta baguette (or ciabatta rolls)
• provolone cheese slices
• onion
• green pepper
• seasoning for the meat: soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder, salt, pepper (measure with your heart)

Here’s what I did:
• slice the onion and pepper, add to a pan with olive oil. Season with salt and pepper
• while the veggies cook, season your meat with soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder, salt and pepper
• add a light coat of mayo to the ciabatta bread and broil for about 3 minutes 
• once the veggies are just about done, add the meat to the same pan and cook until no longer pink
• mix the meat and veggies together and section into portions for the sandwiches 
• add a slice of provolone cheese on top of meat + veggie mixture and melt
• add meat and veggies to the ciabatta roll

Easy, satisfying lunch (or breakfast) idea - save this post for later!

Nick sent me this recipe and we immediately had to try it. The feta gets golden brown on the bottom and the egg yolk acts as a sauce for the wrap. So delicious!!

Here’s what you need:
• tortilla or wrap of your choice
• avocado
• 1 egg
• feta cheese crumbles
• red pepper flakes

Here’s what I did:
• sprinkle feta in a circle into a pan set to medium heat
• crack an egg in the middle of the feta. Push the feta towards the egg if needed so that it sticks to the egg
• let the egg and feta cook until the bottoms are browned and the egg is fully cooked but the yolk is still runny. Sprinkle red pepper flakes on top 
• smash avocado into a warmed tortilla (I heat mine in a cast iron skillet with a little bit of olive oil to get it warm and browned)
• add the cooked egg + feta to the tortilla
• fold in half and squeeze the egg so that the yolk runs over 

Enjoy and follow for more 🤍

Pasta of your choosing

¼ teaspoon of red pepper flakes
Fresh lemon juice from one lemon
½ cup of crumbled feta
⅓ cup of sunflower seeds
Handful of chopped fresh mint leaves
Olive oil
Salt and pepper for seasoning
½ cup of reserved pasta water

Here’s what I did:

Easy Trader Joe’s meals part 41: chicken wonton stir fry. Save this post for later!

These stir fry vegetables are one of my favorites - everything comes pre-chopped so it makes mealtime quicker and easier.

Here’s what you need:
• Asian style vegetable stir fry
• chicken cilantro mini wontons 
• Soyaki sauce
• optional: brown rice (I like the frozen brown rice - it cooks perfectly in the microwave in 3 minutes)
• olive oil
• salt, pepper, garlic powder 

Here’s what I did:
• add some oil to a large pan and dump the entire carton of stir fry vegetables in. Break up any large pieces 
• season with salt, pepper and garlic powder

Freezer breakfast sandwiches - the perfect quick breakfast for postpartum, kids on the go, etc. Save this post for later!

Original recipe is from @tastesbetterfromscratch - I made a few changes 

Here’s what you need:
• 14 eggs
• 3 tablespoons of milk
• 24 pieces of cooked bacon
• 12 English muffins 
• 12 slices of cheese (I did American) 
• 1 teaspoon of salt
• 1/2 teaspoon of pepper
(Makes 12 breakfast sandwiches) 

Here’s what I did:
• preheat the oven to 400°
• line a baking sheet with foil and add the strips of bacon. Bake for 15 minutes, flipping halfway 
• while the bacon cooks, whisk the eggs, milk, salt and pepper in a bowl 
• pour the egg mixture into a greased 9x13 pan
• once the bacon is done, lower the oven temperature to 325° and cook the eggs for 20-25 minutes
• remove the eggs from the oven, let cool, then cut into 12 even squares 
• assemble the sandwiches - top each English muffin with egg, 2 slices of bacon and 1 slice of cheese
• wrap each sandwich individually in foil then place in a freezer bag. Freeze for up to one month
• when you’re ready to eat the sandwiches, place it in the fridge overnight to thaw. In the morning, warm sandwiches in the oven at 350° for 10 minutes. Or remove foil, wrap in a damp paper towel and microwave for 30 seconds at 50% power. Flip and microwave for an additional 15-30 seconds on high.

• top with half of the veggie mix and 1/2 cup of shredded cheese. Repeat

This is the perfect winter meal. The toasted ciabatta for dipping is a must 👌🏼👌🏼

Here’s what you need:
• creamy tomato soup
• party size mini meatballs (in the frozen aisle)
• shredded mozzarella
• ciabatta rolls
• pizza sprinkle seasoning blend
• fresh basil 

Here’s what I did:
• pour the soup into a medium pot over medium heat 
• add the number of meatballs that you want (no need to cook the meatballs first as they’ll cook while the soup heats up)
• mix in 2 tablespoons of pizza sprinkle seasoning blend 
• cook for 15-20 minutes until hot
• cut the basil into thin strips
• pour the soup into a bowl and top with shredded mozzarella, basil and a little more seasoning 
• serve with a toasted ciabatta roll for dipping
